<HEADLINE>
<P>
MURDER TRIAL ORDERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A San Diego man, accused of killing a man he had just met, was ordered Monday 
to stand trial on a murder charge. 
</P>
<P>
Ernest Eugene Scott, 31, of East San Diego is accused of fatally shooting 
Antonio Silva, 33, on July 26 in the garage of Silva's home in on Mt. Herbert 
Avenue in Clairemont. 
</P>
<P>
Scott, who is being held in lieu of $1-million bail, shot Silva during an 
argument, Deputy Dist. Atty. David A. Stutz said. 
</P>
<P>
Testimony during Monday's preliminary hearing indicated that Scott was under 
the influence of methamphetamine. 
</P>
<P>
Scott will be arraigned in Superior Court on Sept. 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
