<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY ROUNDUP: ATLANTA FIRM ACQUIRES PRACTICAL PERIPHERALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Practical Peripherals of Westlake Village was acquired by Hayes Microcomputer 
Products of Atlanta for an undisclosed amount. Both companies produce modems, 
which are used in transmitting computer data. 
</P>
<P>
As a result of the acquisition, the companies settled a lawsuit in which Hayes 
had claimed that Practical infringed on a Hayes modem patent. Practical had 
asserted that the patent was invalid. 
</P>
<P>
Michael Seedman, Practical's chief executive, predicted that Practical's sales 
for the year that will end Aug. 31 would be $20 million. Hayes would not 
disclose the Georgia company's sales. Practical's management will remain 
intact, said Seedman and Hayes President Dennis C. Hayes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
