VALLEY ROUNDUP: DATAPRODUCTS CORP. DELAYS MEETING TO STUDY OPTIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dataproducts Corp., a Woodland Hills-based maker of computer printers, 
postponed its annual meeting from Thursday to Sept. 14 in order to consider 
options for "maximizing shareholder value." 
</P>
<P>
On Aug. 3, a New York investor group with an 8% stake in Dataproducts offered 
$273 million for the rest of the company. The group, DPC Acquisition Partners, 
also made two alternative offers to acquire parts of the company. 
</P>
<P>
Dataproducts then announced plans to sell its 21.5-acre headquarters property 
for $63 million. The New York investors said earlier that if they were 
successful in buying Dataproducts, they had planned to sell the property for 
$57 million. 
