<HEADLINE>
<P>
1,000 MORE E. GERMANS FLEE TO AUSTRIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
VIENNA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
More than 1,000 East Germans managed to slip into Austria through Hungary's 
relaxed border over the weekend, a West German Embassy spokesman said Monday in 
Vienna. 
</P>
<P>
Early Monday, another 150 East Germans had arrived at the embassy to apply for 
papers allowing them to travel to West Germany, he said, adding: "The flood is 
continuing." 
</P>
<P>
More than 3,000 East Germans have managed to cross into Austria from Hungary 
since mid-May, when Budapest began dismantling its fortified border with 
Austria, he said. He added that some traveled directly to West Germany, 
bypassing Vienna. 
</P>
<P>
Several hundred East Germans attending a symbolic picnic on the 
Austro-Hungarian border Saturday managed to slip into Austria through an open 
border crossing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
