</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BODIES OF LELAND, 8 OTHERS ON WAY HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, Ethiopia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The bodies of Texas congressman Mickey Leland and eight other Americans killed 
Aug. 7 in a plane crash will arrive in the United States on Wednesday, U.S. and 
Ethiopian officials said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Leland and 15 others died when the Twin Otter plane taking them to an Ethiopian 
refugee camp flew into a mountain in bad weather. It took searchers a week to 
find the wreckage. 
</P>
<P>
In Washington, State Department spokesman Richard Boucher said the remains of 
the victims are being flown from the Ethiopian capital of Addis Ababa to 
Frankfurt, West Germany, then on to Andrews Air Force Base just outside 
Washington. 
</P>
<P>
Leland, a Democrat, had represented a Houston district since 1978 and was 
chairman of the House Select Committee on Hunger. 
</P>
