<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: TRANSIENT KILLED IN FALL IN PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man believed to be a transient slipped and fell about 150 feet to his death 
in Griffith Park, Los Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
A jogger found the unidentified man at 6:20 a.m. Monday and alerted park 
rangers, Detective Sam Catalfamo said. Catalfamo said broken plants indicate 
that the man fell from a path. 
</P>
<P>
Investigators believe the man is one of 30 to 40 transients living in the park. 
</P>
