<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: BLAZE KILLS MAN IN BOARDED-UP HOUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One man died of smoke inhalation and another was in intensive care Monday after 
a fire in the boarded-up house in Eagle Rock where they were sleeping, Los 
Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
"It appears that they might have set fire to one end of the house to keep warm 
and slept on the other side," said Detective John Munguia. 
</P>
<P>
The fire started on a porch on the opposite side. Because the windows were 
boarded, the smoke had no where to escape, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Firefighters were called to the house on Eagle Rock Boulevard about 5 a.m. but 
did not discover the men until several hours later, Munguia said. The two 
unidentified victims, between 25 and 30 years old, apparently were transients, 
he said. 
</P>
<P>
The survivor was in the intensive care unit at Glendale Memorial Hospital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
