<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: GIRL SHOT IN FOOT; POLICE BLAME GANGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gunfire from a passing car wounded a 1-year-old girl in the left foot as she 
stood in the doorway of her home in the Koreatown area of Los Angeles, police 
said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Stacy Arevalo was shot about 10:30 p.m. Sunday and was taken to Children's 
Hospital, where she was listed in stable condition with fractured bones. 
</P>
<P>
The girl's parents, who were in their South Catalina Street house when the 
gunfire occurred, told police they knew of no reason for the attack. Officers 
said they believe Salvadoran gangs in the area were responsible for the 
shooting. 
