<HEADLINE>
<P>
KRAFT WILL BUY FAT SUBSTITUTE FROM NUTRASWEET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
GLENVIEW, Ill. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kraft Foods will buy an experimental fat substitute from NutraSweet Co. to use 
in making mayonnaise and Miracle Whip, the two companies have announced. 
</P>
<P>
Skokie, Ill.-based NutraSweet announced the development of the fat substitute 
Simplesse, which is made from egg whites and skim milk, last year but the 
substance has not yet received Food and Drug Administration approval. 
</P>
<P>
Kraft has developed its own fat substitute -- Trailblazer -- but it plans to 
use that substance in frozen desserts, saying the Simplesse formula is more 
suited to mayonnaise. 
</P>
<P>
Neither company put a price tag on the deal. 
</P>
