<P>
The Organization of African Unity laid down tough conditions for talks with the 
South African government, adopting a nine-page strategy document that endorses 
the known negotiating position of the African National Congress, South Africa's 
main black nationalist group. The document, adopted by an OAU ad hoc committee 
meeting in Harare, Zimbabwe, calls on Pretoria to lift the existing state of 
emergency, free political prisoners, end a ban on political organizations and 
restrictions on individuals, withdraw troops from black townships and end 
political trials and executions. 
