<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOLON FINISHES FIRST IN RACE ACROSS AMERICA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Paul Solon of Tiburon, Calif., won the Race Across AMerica Monday, finishing 
the 2,908-mile bicycle race in 8 days 8 hours 45 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
Solon crossed the finish line in New York City at 11:45 p.m. EST. 
</P>
<P>
He finished well ahead of Mike Secrest of Scottsdale, Ariz. Secrest reached 
Bernardsville, N.J., at 12:40 a.m. today. 
</P>
<P>
Solon had reached Bernardsville at 8:10 p.m. and rested for 15 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
Susan Noporangelo of Harvard, Ill., is the only woman remaining in the race. 
She was in eighth after reaching Grantsville, Md., at 9:57 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
The race began in Costa Mesa on Aug. 13. 
</P>
