LA HABRA'S MOORE SIGNS WITH CUBS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Shortstop Tim Moore of La Habra High School said Monday that he has signed a 
contract with the Chicago Cubs. 
</P>
<P>
Moore, who was a 12th-round selection in the June amateur draft, had planned to 
play at Fullerton College next year. 
</P>
<P>
"I just didn't feel I was ready for college," Moore said. "I kind of wanted to 
give this a shot." 
</P>
<P>
Moore hit .530 for La Habra last season. He was an All-County selection and a 
second-team All-Southern Section pick. 
</P>
<P>
He will begin playing in the Arizona Instructional League on Sept. 15. 
