117 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Burlington Air Express Inc., an international cargo-express company, reported 
an operating profit of $6.1 million for the second quarter, nearly three times 
the $2.1 million posted for the comparable quarter last year. Revenue rose 10%, 
to $211 million from $191.4 million. 
</P>
<P>
"Our strong second-quarter earnings reflect Burlington's service enhancement 
program, gains in our domestic and international market share and contributions 
from our air-cargo charter activities," said David L. Marshall, Burlington's 
chairman and chief executive. 
</P>
<P>
The Irvine-based company, a subsidiary of the Pittston Co., reported that more 
than half of its revenue for the quarter came from international transactions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Corporate Earnings 
</P>
</TYPE>
