<P>
ITALIAN GOLD OPENS WORLD GAMES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DUISBURG, West Germany 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Diana Bianchedi of Italy won the first gold medal of the World University Games 
today, and fencing teammate Giovanna Trillini added a bronze in the women's 
foil. 
</P>
<P>
In the only other event of the opening day, Yugoslavia began the defense of its 
men's basketball title with a 93-52 trouncing of Greece. No other basketball 
matches were scheduled today. 
</P>
<P>
The University Games, shifted to Duisburg from Sao Paulo five months ago when 
the Brazilian city pulled out for lack of money, have been scaled down to four 
sports -- fencing, basketball, rowing and track and field. 
</P>
</TEXT>
